The two .in templates in this directory are taken verbatim from

    https://github.com/InioX/matugen-themes  (MIT)
    templates/kvantum-colors.kvconfig
    templates/kvantum-colors.svg

Only the file names changed. They are vendored rather than fetched so an apply
never depends on the network, and rendered by scripts/apply-theme.sh, which
substitutes {{colors.<role>.default.hex}} with the corresponding DMS Theme
role. Kvantum needs both files: the .kvconfig carries text and base colours,
the .svg draws every widget, and neither contains a single hard-coded hex.

